            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod%20knew%20that%20people%20would%20battle%20two%20major%20enemies%3A%20pride%20and%20selfishness.%20He%20dealt%20with%20humanity's%20pride%20at%20Babel%20(Genesis%2011%3A1-9)%2C%20and%20in%20Genesis%2014%20He%20dealt%20with%20humanity's%20selfishness.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAbraham%20was%20the%20first%20man%20recorded%20in%20the%20Scriptures%20to%20tithe%2C%20although%20Abel%20did%20offer%20the%20Lord%20%22choice%20lambs%20from%20the%20best%20of%20his%20flock%22%20(Genesis%204%3A4).%20Abraham's%20worship%20of%20God%20with%20ten%20percent%20of%20his%20revenue%20showed%20that%20he%20acknowledged%20his%20financial%20responsibility%20before%20God%20and%20knew%20that%20God%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20would%20take%20care%20of%20his%20needs.%20By%20refusing%20the%20king%20of%20Sodom's%20reward%20(Genesis%2014%3A21-23)%2C%20Abraham%20rejected%20the%20world's%20system.%20God%20became%20his%20reward%20(his%20salary%2C%20wages%2C%20and%20compensation)%2C%20and%20God%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20recompensed%20Abraham%20with%20something%20that%20money%20could%20not%20buy%3A%20a%20child!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETithing%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20Abraham's%20covenant%20with%20God.%20God%20reciprocated%20and%20pledged%20all%20His%20assets%20to%20Abraham%2C%20even%20unto%20the%20fourth%20generation%20(Genesis%2015%3A14-16).%20Abraham%20further%20exemplified%20an%20unselfish%20spirit%20when%20he%20gave%20Lot%20the%20first%20choice%20of%20where%20to%20live.%20The%20final%20result%20was%20that%20Abraham%20profited%20much%20more%20than%20Lot%20because%20he%20obeyed%20the%20principle%20of%20unselfish%20sacrifice%20for%20others%20(Genesis%2013).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWant%20to%20be%20blessed%3F%20Be%20a%20tither!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Genesis.13:5-15:21",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EGenesis%2013%3A5-15%3A21%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ELot%2C%20who%20was%20traveling%20with%20Abram%2C%20had%20also%20become%20very%20wealthy%20with%20flocks%20of%20sheep%20and%20goats%2C%20herds%20of%20cattle%2C%20and%20many%20tents.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20land%20could%20not%20support%20both%20Abram%20and%20Lot%20with%20all%20their%20flocks%20and%20herds%20living%20so%20close%20together.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20disputes%20broke%20out%20between%20the%20herdsmen%20of%20Abram%20and%20Lot.%20(At%20that%20time%20Canaanites%20and%20Perizzites%20were%20also%20living%20in%20the%20land.)%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EFinally%20Abram%20said%20to%20Lot%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%26%23x2019%3Bs%20not%20allow%20this%20conflict%20to%20come%20between%20us%20or%20our%20herdsmen.%20After%20all%2C%20we%20are%20close%20relatives!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_9%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20whole%20countryside%20is%20open%20to%20you.%20Take%20your%20choice%20of%20any%20section%20of%20the%20land%20you%20want%2C%20and%20we%20will%20separate.%20If%20you%20want%20the%20land%20to%20the%20left%2C%20then%20I%26%23x2019%3Bll%20take%20the%20land%20on%20the%20right.%20If%20you%20prefer%20the%20land%20on%20the%20right%2C%20then%20I%26%23x2019%3Bll%20go%20to%20the%20left.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_10%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ELot%20took%20a%20long%20look%20at%20the%20fertile%20plains%20of%20the%20Jordan%20Valley%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Zoar.%20The%20whole%20area%20was%20well%20watered%20everywhere%2C%20like%20the%20garden%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20or%20the%20beautiful%20land%20of%20Egypt.%20(This%20was%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20destroyed%20Sodom%20and%20Gomorrah.)%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_11%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ELot%20chose%20for%20himself%20the%20whole%20Jordan%20Valley%20to%20the%20east%20of%20them.%20He%20went%20there%20with%20his%20flocks%20and%20servants%20and%20parted%20company%20with%20his%20uncle%20Abram.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_12%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Abram%20settled%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Canaan%2C%20and%20Lot%20moved%20his%20tents%20to%20a%20place%20near%20Sodom%20and%20settled%20among%20the%20cities%20of%20the%20plain.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_13%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20people%20of%20this%20area%20were%20extremely%20wicked%20and%20constantly%20sinned%20against%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_14%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20Lot%20had%20gone%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20Abram%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLook%20as%20far%20as%20you%20can%20see%20in%20every%20direction%26%23x2014%3Bnorth%20and%20south%2C%20east%20and%20west.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_15%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20am%20giving%20all%20this%20land%2C%20as%20far%20as%20you%20can%20see%2C%20to%20you%20and%20your%20descendants%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eseed%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2013%3A16.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20a%20permanent%20possession.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_16%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20I%20will%20give%20you%20so%20many%20descendants%20that%2C%20like%20the%20dust%20of%20the%20earth%2C%20they%20cannot%20be%20counted!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_17%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EGo%20and%20walk%20through%20the%20land%20in%20every%20direction%2C%20for%20I%20am%20giving%20it%20to%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_13_18%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Abram%20moved%20his%20camp%20to%20Hebron%20and%20settled%20near%20the%20oak%20grove%20belonging%20to%20Mamre.%20There%20he%20built%20another%20altar%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_1%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EGenesis%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAbram%20Rescues%20Lot%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAbout%20this%20time%20war%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20region.%20King%20Amraphel%20of%20Babylonia%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E14%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EShinar%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2014%3A9.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20King%20Arioch%20of%20Ellasar%2C%20King%20Kedorlaomer%20of%20Elam%2C%20and%20King%20Tidal%20of%20Goiim%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_2%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3Efought%20against%20King%20Bera%20of%20Sodom%2C%20King%20Birsha%20of%20Gomorrah%2C%20King%20Shinab%20of%20Admah%2C%20King%20Shemeber%20of%20Zeboiim%2C%20and%20the%20king%20of%20Bela%20(also%20called%20Zoar).%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_3%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20second%20group%20of%20kings%20joined%20forces%20in%20Siddim%20Valley%20(that%20is%2C%20the%20valley%20of%20the%20Dead%20Sea%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E14%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ESalt%20Sea.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E).%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_4%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20twelve%20years%20they%20had%20been%20subject%20to%20King%20Kedorlaomer%2C%20but%20in%20the%20thirteenth%20year%20they%20rebelled%20against%20him.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20year%20later%20Kedorlaomer%20and%20his%20allies%20arrived%20and%20defeated%20the%20Rephaites%20at%20Ashteroth-karnaim%2C%20the%20Zuzites%20at%20Ham%2C%20the%20Emites%20at%20Shaveh-kiriathaim%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20the%20Horites%20at%20Mount%20Seir%2C%20as%20far%20as%20El-paran%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20wilderness.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20they%20turned%20back%20and%20came%20to%20En-mishpat%20(now%20called%20Kadesh)%20and%20conquered%20all%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Amalekites%2C%20and%20also%20the%20Amorites%20living%20in%20Hazazon-tamar.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20rebel%20kings%20of%20Sodom%2C%20Gomorrah%2C%20Admah%2C%20Zeboiim%2C%20and%20Bela%20(also%20called%20Zoar)%20prepared%20for%20battle%20in%20the%20valley%20of%20the%20Dead%20Sea.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E14%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ESiddim%20Valley%3C%2Fem%3E%20(see%2014%3A3)%3B%20also%20in%2014%3A10.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_9%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20fought%20against%20King%20Kedorlaomer%20of%20Elam%2C%20King%20Tidal%20of%20Goiim%2C%20King%20Amraphel%20of%20Babylonia%2C%20and%20King%20Arioch%20of%20Ellasar%26%23x2014%3Bfour%20kings%20against%20five.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_10%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20it%20happened%2C%20the%20valley%20of%20the%20Dead%20Sea%20was%20filled%20with%20tar%20pits.%20And%20as%20the%20army%20of%20the%20kings%20of%20Sodom%20and%20Gomorrah%20fled%2C%20some%20fell%20into%20the%20tar%20pits%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20escaped%20into%20the%20mountains.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_11%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20victorious%20invaders%20then%20plundered%20Sodom%20and%20Gomorrah%20and%20headed%20for%20home%2C%20taking%20with%20them%20all%20the%20spoils%20of%20war%20and%20the%20food%20supplies.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_12%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20captured%20Lot%26%23x2014%3BAbram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20nephew%20who%20lived%20in%20Sodom%26%23x2014%3Band%20carried%20off%20everything%20he%20owned.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_13%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20one%20of%20Lot%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20escaped%20and%20reported%20everything%20to%20Abram%20the%20Hebrew%2C%20who%20was%20living%20near%20the%20oak%20grove%20belonging%20to%20Mamre%20the%20Amorite.%20Mamre%20and%20his%20relatives%2C%20Eshcol%20and%20Aner%2C%20were%20Abram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_14_14%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2214%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Abram%20heard%20that%20his%20nephew%20Lot%20had%20been%20captured%2C%20he%20mobilized%20the%20318%26%23xA0%3Btrained%20men%20who%20had%20been%20born%20into%20his%20household.%20Then%20he%20pursued%20Kedorlaomer%26%23x2019%3Bs%20army%20until%20he%20caught%20up%20with%20them%20at%2